            <h1>                <a href='/en/dep/fin/News/news/2010/ilo-and-imf-conference-in-oslo-to-addres.html?id=612489'>ILO and IMF conference in Oslo</a>            </h1>            <div class="ArticleContent"><p>A joint conference with The International Labour Organization (ILO) and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) was hosted by the Prime Minister of Norway, Jens Stoltenberg, 13 September 2010, in Oslo.</p>
<p>The conference on “The Challenges of Growth, Employment and Social Cohesion”, the first of its kind, explored new ways of forging a sustainable, job-rich recovery from the global economic crisis.</p></div>                                    
            
            
            
        </div>
        <div id="FPMainArticle" class='FPSmall'>
            <div class="ArticleContent">Several targeted policy measures helped mitigating the effects of the international financial crisis on the Norwegian economy. Following a decline in mainland output of 1.4 per cent in 2009, growth in the Mainland economy is now forecast at 1.7 per cent in 2010 and 3.1 per cent in 2011, the latter about half a percentage point above trend growth. Unemployment has been kept at low levels throughout the downturn and is forecast at 3½ per cent both in 2010 and 2011.</div>
            
            <h2 Style="font-size:2.0em;">
                
                <a href='/en/dep/fin/press-center/Press-releases/2010/fiscal-budget-2011-a-modest-fiscal-tight.html?id=619723' style="font-weight:bold;"><p>Fiscal Budget 2011: A modest fiscal tightening</p></a>
                </h2>
            <p class="ArticleComment">(Ministry of Finance, 05.10.2010)</p>
        </div>        
        <img src="/upload/PORTAL/Portrettbilder/165x250/sigbjorn_johnsen_b_165x250.jpg" alt="Minister of Finance, Sigbjørn Johnsen" class="FPMainImg" />
        
    </div>

